The paper discusses the problem of configuring nodal elements of a distributed dynamical system to achieve a global goal, which is a common problem in the field of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a mathematical theory for designing such systems, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.MA). The concept of collective intelligence is also mentioned, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the El Farol bar problem, which is a classic example of a coordination problem in multi-agent systems (cs.SI).
